<div1 type="letter">

<pb facs="nei.j4c.49.11-13_0001a" />

<note type="curatorial">Aly Collection
245-2</note>

<opener>
<dateline>
Aug. 18, 66
</dateline>

<salute>Dear Lucile:</salute>
</opener>
<p>I <hi rend="underline">do</hi> greatly miss hearing from you!</p>

<p>The affair at Bancroft was an astonishing success! There were nearly 1500 in the crowd, and the Pageant (from Black Elk) was a joy. The whole crowd seemed to be enveloped in an atmosphere of affection and happiness.</p>

<pb facs="nei.j4c.49.11-13_0001b"/>
<fw type="authorial">-2-</fw>

<p>The lectures at <del>Wayne</del><add>Wayne</add> (two weeks) went off in great shape. They had a sculptor on hand to make a new bust of me. It is really good. It is to be unveiled (in bronze) at Homecoming Oct. 14. At the time there will be a parade of 42 floats, each representing some scene from the <hi rend="double underline">Cycle</hi>.</p>

<note type="authorial">(inside)</note>  <fw type="curatorial">11</fw>

<pb facs="nei.j4c.49.11-13_0002"/>
<fw type="authorial">-3-</fw>

<closer>
<salute>With the old affection &#8212;</salute> 

<signed>John N.</signed>
</closer>

</div1>


